-- Taiwan Stocks: AU Optronics, China Petroleum, Hon Hai Precision
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-04-11T05:50:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-11/taiwan-stocks-au-optronics-taiwan-semiconductor-manufacturing.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The benchmark Taiex Index rose 0.2 percent to 7,656.67.  AU Optronics Corp. (2409)  (2409 TT) dropped 1 percent to NT$14.55.
The flat-panel maker’s first-quarter consolidated revenue was
NT$81.1 billion ($2.75 billion), compared with NT$93.2 billion a
year earlier, according to a statement to the  Taiwan Stock
Exchange .  China Petrochemical Development Corp. (1314)  (1314 TT), a chemical
producer, jumped 6.9 percent to NT$33.5, the biggest gain since
Jan. 5. The board approved plans to pay a cash dividend of
NT$1.75 a share for 2011 and a stock dividend of 17.5 percent,
it said in statements to the Taiwan stock exchange yesterday.  Hon Hai Precision Industry Co. (2317)  (2317 TT) gained 3.2 percent
to NT$113.50. Sales at the world’s largest electronics maker
rose 30 percent in March from a year earlier, according to an
exchange filing.  Sino-American Silicon Products Inc. (5483)  (5483 TT) surged 6.9
percent to NT$52.70, the steepest gain since Jan. 30. The
provider of silicon used in solar cells reported March sales at
NT$398 million, compared with NT$369 million in February,
according to exchange filings.  To contact the reporter on this story:
